AU  - Carr, Peter
AU  - Wu, Liuren
Y1  - 2003/12/01
PY  - 2003
DA  - 2003/12/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1046/j.1540-6261.2003.00616.x
T2  - The Journal of Finance
JF  - The Journal of Finance
JO  - The Journal of Finance
JA  - The Journal of Finance
SP  - 2581
EP  - 2610
VL  - 58
IS  - 6
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0022-1082
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1046/j.1540-6261.2003.00616.x
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - Abstract We develop a simple robust method to distinguish the presence of continuous and discontinuous components in the price of an asset underlying options. Our method examines the prices of at-the-money and out-of-the-money options as the option's time-to-maturity approaches zero. We show that these prices converge to zero at speeds that depend upon whether the underlying asset price process is purely continuous, purely discontinuous, or a combination of both. We apply the method to S&P 500 index options and find the existence of both a continuous component and a jump component in the index.
ER  - 

